::[Doctor] Although the cold clothes may cause an impression that they are further negatively affecting the victims of hypothermia, in critical situations, only the wet clothes should be removed, while the rest should stay on as they are still providing a minuscule cover. ::

::[Doctor] Hypothermia causes a huge strain on the heart as the body needs to maintain temperature. As such, the process of applying outside heat should be done so carefully near the heart and then gradually expanded outwards. Areas around the chest, armpits, neck and groin would be the best places to start working on. ::

::[Doctor] Any sudden change of temperature may cause fatal consequences to the rhythm of heart. The goal in cold environments should be to maintain stable heart rate with as least deviations as possible. Therefore, controlled intake of warm drinks, preferably water, is the best approach.::

::[Doctor] When human tissue is exposed to cold, its characteristics change, weakening it in the process. Rapid movement of affected body parts may cause fatal injuries. If need arises to move a victim away from the source of cold, it should be done so slowly. ::

::[Doctor] Victims affected by frostbite may show signs of desperation as the body slowly starts to give in. Falling to sleep in critical situations is therefore something that should be avoided at all costs. In addition, maintaining vertical body position may further help with blood flow, helping to warm up the victim.::
